    <center><h1>Command Execution</h1></center>

    <hr>
    <a name="CommandRunner"></a>
    <h2>class CommandRunner</h2>

    <h3>#include "CommandRunner.h"</h3>

    The CommandRunner class can be used to execute shell commands from a C++ program.

    <h3>Methods</h3>

	<h3>static void Run(const string &amp; commandText);</h3>
	Executes the passed-in command string.  If the command fails (i.e., returns a non-zero
	value from main), a CS240Exception is thrown.
	<p>
	Example:
	<pre>
	CommandRunner::Run("g++ -o hello HelloWorld.cpp");</pre>
	
	<p>

